div.p:
A meeting was held in the office of Mr. Moore, May 3, 1935, to discuss the matter
                    of negotiations regarding the possible establishment of a trans-Atlantic air
                    transport service. Those present were: 

Representing the Department of State: 

Mr. R. Walton Moore, Assistant Secretary of State;

Mr. Richard Southgate;

Mr. J. Pierrepont Moffat;

Mr. Stephen Latchford.



Representing the Pan American Airways: 

Mr. Juan T. Trippe, President, Pan American Airways;

Mr. John C. Cooper, Jr., Vice President, Pan American
                                    Airways.
